Conforming to these ideas is destructive 
We cut away at self-worth until thereâ€™s nothing left 
but the molded person you confined into being. 
Not even realizing youâ€™re meant to be so much more.

We compare ourselves to these false goddesses, manipulated and altered.
As if theyâ€™ll teach us how not to need.
As if theyâ€™ll teach us how to be loved.
Be your own goddess, find beauty in yourself before others.â€

[{'node': {'text': "Had the pleasure of designing and tattooing a #trashpolkatattoo .
.
.
The client wanted a compass tattoo, I asked if he would like anything to go with it, he wasn't sure he said, so I asked him what his thoughts were on brush strokes, he didn't dislike them he said common ground, leave it to me I said. That was pretty much how it went down. Jokes aside though, I don't get people that see a tattoo and want the exact same one, where's your sense of creativity that's what the tattoo artist is there for. It's cool if you found a tattoo you like and show it to your tattoo artist to get him on the right track, but if you straight up copy someone's tattoo that's just lame you aren't showing who you are, you are just showing what or who you like to copy.
.
